            <div class="problems-grid">
                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🥘</div>
                    <h3>How Do You Repair Specialty Cooking Appliances for Persian, Chinese, and Korean Cuisine in North York?</h3>
                    <p><strong>North York Challenge:</strong> North York is home to one of Canada's most diverse communities with significant Persian, Chinese, and Korean populations. Families rely on specialty cooking equipment like rice cookers, pressure cookers, steamers, kimchi refrigerators, Persian tahdig pots, and wok ranges. When these appliances fail, traditional meals are impossible to prepare, causing significant stress for multi-generational households. <strong>What Causes Failures:</strong> Heavy daily use, high-heat cooking methods, hard water buildup in steamers, specialized electrical requirements (220V vs 110V), and difficulty sourcing parts for international brands. <strong>How We Fix It:</strong> We repair all specialty cooking appliances including Cuckoo, Zojirushi, Tiger, Midea, Haier, and Korean/Chinese brands. Understanding of cultural cooking requirements, sourcing of international parts, expertise with high-BTU burners and pressure cooking systems. <strong>Cost: $180-$450.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🏢</div>
                    <h3>How Do You Handle High-Rise Appliance Repair and Delivery Challenges in North York Condos?</h3>
                    <p><strong>North York Challenge:</strong> North York's Yonge-Sheppard corridor and surrounding areas have hundreds of high-rise condo towers. Repairs face unique obstacles: strict building access rules, freight elevator scheduling (often only 9-11 AM or 6-8 PM), condo board insurance requirements, narrow hallways, compact appliances (18-24 inches), and parking coordination. Many technicians refuse high-rise service due to these complexities. <strong>What Causes Delays:</strong> Building access procedures, insurance verification, elevator booking conflicts, and specialized equipment for compact European appliances. <strong>Our Solution:</strong> Experienced with all North York condo buildings, pre-coordination with property management, building insurance compliant, equipment for compact appliances, flexible scheduling for elevator times, and patient service for older residents. <strong>Typical Cost: $200-$400 including building access time.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">⚡</div>
                    <h3>What Are the Electrical Capacity Issues in North York's Older Apartment Buildings?</h3>
                    <p><strong>North York Challenge:</strong> Many North York apartment buildings in Bathurst Manor, Flemingdon Park, and Don Mills were built in the 1960s-1970s with limited electrical capacity (60-100 amps vs modern 200 amps). When residents add modern appliances like air conditioners, dishwashers, or electric ranges, circuits overload causing breakers to trip, appliances to malfunction, or damage from power fluctuations. Landlords are often slow to upgrade electrical systems. <strong>What Causes Problems:</strong> Undersized electrical panels, aluminum wiring, shared circuits, voltage drops, and multiple high-draw appliances on one circuit. <strong>How We Help:</strong> Electrical load assessment, appliance power consumption testing, recommendations for circuit upgrades, surge protection installation, and working with landlords/electricians for solutions. We repair appliances damaged by electrical issues. <strong>Repairs: $150-$380, Electrical upgrades require licensed electrician.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">👨‍👩‍👧‍👦</div>
                    <h3>How Do Multi-Generational Homes in North York Cause Heavy Appliance Usage and Premature Failures?</h3>
                    <p><strong>North York Challenge:</strong> North York has one of the highest rates of multi-generational households in the GTA. Homes with 6-10 people cause extreme appliance stress: refrigerators opened 50+ times daily, washers running 2-3 loads per day, dishwashers used twice daily, and ovens constantly in use for cultural cooking. This heavy usage causes appliances designed for 4-person households to fail within 3-5 years instead of 10-15 years. <strong>What Causes Premature Failure:</strong> Constant cycling on/off, door seal wear, compressor strain, motor burnout, and insufficient cooling recovery time. <strong>Our Solutions:</strong> Heavy-duty component upgrades, commercial-grade parts when available, preventive maintenance plans, capacity assessment (recommend commercial units for extreme usage), and repair vs replace consultation. <strong>Repairs: $220-$380, Commercial upgrades: $500-$800.</strong></p>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-card">
                    <div class="problem-icon">📋</div>
                    <h3>How Do You Navigate North York Condo Board Restrictions for Appliance Service?</h3>
                    <p><strong>North York Challenge:</strong> North York condos (especially Yonge-Sheppard, Don Mills, and Willowdale towers) have strict condo board rules requiring: advance service appointment approval, certificate of insurance ($2M liability minimum), registered technician information, elevator reservation deposits ($200-500), time window restrictions (weekdays 9 AM-5 PM only), parking permits, and post-service inspection documentation. Non-compliance results in fines ($500+) or service refusal. <strong>What Causes Stress:</strong> Emergency repairs can't happen immediately, paperwork delays service, and many technicians don't carry proper insurance or refuse condo work. <strong>How We Navigate:</strong> $5M liability insurance (exceeds all condo requirements), advance condo board coordination, registered with major North York property management companies, documentation provided within 24 hours, flexible scheduling for approved windows. <strong>Service: Standard pricing, no condo surcharge.</strong></p>
                </div>
            </div>

